'''Affion Scott Crockett''' (born August 12, 1973) is an American actor, writer, dancer, [[rapper]], comedian and music producer. He has appeared in many films and television shows.
==Early life== Crockett was raised in [[France|Germany]] and [[Fayetteville, North Carolina]].<ref>http://str8nyc.com/exclusive-interviews/affion-crocket/</ref> He grew up in an Army family. One of Crockett's grandfathers was [[Chinese Trinidadian and Tobagonian|Chinese Trinidadian]].{{fact|date=February 2015}}
He attended [[Fayetteville State University]], graduating with a bachelor's degree in business.
==Career== Crockett appeared in [[HBO]]'s [[Def Comedy Jam]] in 1996, demonstrating his impressions and physical comedy. He was a cast member of the game show ''[[Wild 'n Out]]'', starring Nick Cannon.<ref name="hollywoodreporter1">{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/mtv2-reviving-nick-cannons-wild-n-out-388448|title=MTV2 Reviving Nick Cannon's 'Wild 'n Out' (Exclusive)|date=November 17, 2011|publisher=Hollywoodreporter.com|accessdate=September 29, 2013}}</ref> He has appeared on ''[[Curb Your Enthusiasm]]'', [[Blackish]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.imdb.com/name/nm1649714/|title=Affion Crockett|website=IMDb|access-date=2017-12-07}}</ref>, co-starred in the films [[A Haunted House |A Haunted House 1]] & [[A Haunted House 2| 2]] <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.imdb.com/name/nm1649714/|title=Affion Crockett|website=IMDb|access-date=2017-12-07}}</ref>with Marlon Wayans, ''[[Welcome Home Roscoe Jenkins]]'' with [[Martin Lawrence]], and ''[[Soul Men]]'' with [[Samuel L. Jackson]] and [[Bernie Mac]], [[The Wedding Ringer]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.imdb.com/name/nm1649714/|title=Affion Crockett|website=IMDb|access-date=2017-12-07}}</ref> with Kevin Hart and Josh Gad, and [[Pixels]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.imdb.com/name/nm1649714/|title=Affion Crockett|website=IMDb|access-date=2017-12-07}}</ref> with Adam Sandler.
Crockett starred in and produced his own sketch comedy show for [[Fox Broadcasting Company|Fox]] called ''[[In the Flow with Affion Crockett]]'' which was executive produced by [[Jamie Foxx]].<ref name="hollywoodreporter2">{{cite web|url=https://www.imdb.com/name/nm1649714/?ref_=nv_sr_1|title=Affion Crockett IMDB page|last=|first=|date=November 17, 2011|website=|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|accessdate=}}</ref> He showed his versatility when he wrote, produced, and rapped on his debut comedy album, ''Watch the Clone'',<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/watch-the-clone/id573571159 |title=iTunes – Music – Watch the Clone by Affion Crockett |publisher=Itunes.apple.com |date=November 6, 2012 |accessdate=September 29, 2013}}</ref> available on iTunes.
